              {
                "start_s": 52.175,
                "end_s": 81.875,
                "text": "You had that hot finish there the second quarter. How did you try to make sure that you didn't have the big letdown coming out of halftime? Well, we just talked at half about how we got through that quarter because we were really good defensively. We got after them a little bit, and our defense turned into offense. And we tried to carry that through the second half. And Campbell came in, and they made a lot of shots. And Cammie Curtis finishes with dang near 30, I think. But we limited everybody else. We were great on the basketball. It was our defense that carried us through the game. Obviously, we shot the ball well, but we had to get stops, and we got them."
              },
              {
                "start_s": 82.381,
                "end_s": 103.306,
                "text": "As much as nobody likes to lose, was maybe losing that regional championship game kind of a blessing in disguise considering how the state bracket was shaped and how you went through it? We had to beat really good teams to win, and we knew that regardless. So whoever we got in the first round, second round, third round, we knew we were going to have to beat good teams, and the kids stepped up and did that."
              },
